Sample laugh in
https://iot4kids.com/2014/10/21/easy-arduino-halloween-project-motion-sensing-pumpkin-with-an-evil-laugh/

Parts list:

Arduino
HC-SR04 sonar rangefinder, also called a PING sensor
 (or any other rangefinder or PIR motion detector you might prefer)
speaker, with some way of connecting it to an arduino
  (e.g. bare solid-core wires soldered to both terminals,
  or a connector/plug if you want to get fancy)
amp?
power supply, e.g. 9v battery and plug

Single transistor amps:
https://bryanduxbury.com/2012/01/20/one-transistor-audio-amplifier-for-arduino-projects/
https://forum.arduino.cc/index.php?topic=370964.0
https://www.hackster.io/jwzumwalt/single-transistor-audio-amp-32033a

(more complicated, basic but real class A amplifier circuits)
